      • fetchNextGoal

        public Goal fetchNextGoal()
        Fetches the goal state pointed to by this junction, much like the regular Goal method but with a key difference: the returned goal is the result specified in the junction's ocnfig. This is where branching occurs. No checks are made to predict cycles, etc.

        If none of the kept paths are completed when thsi call is made, will return the next state pointed to by the first path this Junction has.

        Overrides:
        fetchNextGoal in class Goal
        Returns:

      • getKeys

        public java.lang.String getKeys()
        Returns any questKeys the first completed path has. If no paths are completed, returns keys from the first path in the defined path list.
        Overrides:
        getKeys in class Goal
        Returns:
        A string with the key, or null if there isn't one
